# GitHub Linguist classification
# ------------------------------
# kroopt is a Lean 4 project. The cryptographic primitives are NOT written here:
# Kroopt/Native/hacl/ is Project Everest's HACL*/EverCrypt (with the KaRaMeL C
# runtime), vendored verbatim under its upstream licenses (see THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md
# and Kroopt/Native/hacl/). Marking it `linguist-vendored` keeps every byte and its
# license in the tree and in production builds, while excluding it from GitHub's
# language statistics so the repository is classified by its own Lean 4 sources rather
# than the borrowed C.
Kroopt/Native/hacl/** linguist-vendored

# The KaRaMeL-generated C headers under the vendored tree are also not hand-written
# here; the rule above already covers them. Our own thin FFI/socket shim
# (Kroopt/Native/*.c, *.h) is first-party and intentionally counted.
